replies.body:
Doesn't spellvamp cap at 40%? Pretty sure it does, so if you're building a vamp item, you're just wasting runes and masteries on Morg.

I also run a 15/0/15 build as support on {{champion:143}} {{champion:99}} {{champion:61}} {{champion:25}} {{champion:37}} 

I'll sometimes swap to that mastery setup if I'm playing any of those champ in mid against something like a {{champion:238}} {{champion:90}} {{champion:157}} {{champion:31}} {{champion:84}} 

It works to hold a lane when you probably won't be winning it anyway. It's also useful against AD champs when building a {{item:3174}} is not helpful. You can actually rush a {{item:3157}} and not be permanently oom, or you can build a {{item:3070}} first and move on to pure damage.
